[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

00:35.828 --> 00:37.663
>> WHAT IN THE WORLD?!

00:39.540 --> 00:40.791
[ GASPS ]

00:55.597 --> 00:58.017
♪ A ROUTINE PATROL

00:55.597 --> 00:58.017
WITH FOUR BOTS IN STASIS ♪

00:58.141 --> 01:00.728
♪ YEARS LATER AWOKE IN

00:58.141 --> 01:00.728
THE STRANGEST OF PLACES ♪

01:00.853 --> 01:03.313
♪ EARTH WAS THEIR HOME NOW,

01:00.853 --> 01:03.313
AND IN ADDITION ♪

01:03.438 --> 01:05.941
♪ OPTIMUS PRIME GAVE THEM

01:03.438 --> 01:05.941
THIS MISSION ♪

01:06.066 --> 01:08.652
♪ LEARN FROM THE HUMANS,

01:06.066 --> 01:08.652
SERVE AND PROTECT ♪

01:08.777 --> 01:10.863
♪ LIVE IN THEIR WORLD,

01:08.777 --> 01:10.863
EARN THEIR RESPECT ♪

01:10.988 --> 01:13.532
♪ A FAMILY OF HEROES

01:10.988 --> 01:13.532
WILL BE YOUR ALLIES ♪

01:13.657 --> 01:16.326
♪ TO OTHERS,

01:13.657 --> 01:16.326
REMAIN ROBOTS IN DISGUISE ♪

01:16.451 --> 01:18.996
♪ RESCUE BOTS,

01:16.451 --> 01:18.996
ROLL TO THE RESCUE ♪

01:19.120 --> 01:21.289
♪ HUMANS IN NEED,

01:19.120 --> 01:21.289
HEROES, INDEED ♪

01:21.415 --> 01:24.292
♪ RESCUE BOTS,

01:21.415 --> 01:24.292
ROLL TO THE RESCUE ♪

01:24.418 --> 01:26.670
♪ RESCUE BOTS ♪

01:26.795 --> 01:29.088
♪ WITH CODY TO GUIDE THEM

01:26.795 --> 01:29.088
AND SHOW THEM THE WAY ♪

01:29.214 --> 01:31.759
♪ THE RESCUE BOTS

01:29.214 --> 01:31.759
WILL BE SAVING THE DAY ♪

01:31.884 --> 01:34.720
♪ RESCUE BOTS,

01:31.884 --> 01:34.720
ROLL TO THE RESCUE ♪

01:34.845 --> 01:36.513
♪ RESCUE BOTS ♪

01:42.853 --> 01:44.479
>> THE SIEGE HAPPENED WITHOUT

01:44.605 --> 01:46.648
WARNING.

01:46.774 --> 01:47.983
>> WAIT A MINUTE.

01:48.108 --> 01:49.150
WHEN WAS THIS?

01:49.276 --> 01:50.360
>> 200 YEARS AGO.

01:50.485 --> 01:51.361
>> [ SCOFFS ]

01:51.486 --> 01:52.654
ANCIENT HISTORY.

01:52.780 --> 01:54.865
>> SOME OF US WOULD LIKE TO HEAR

01:54.990 --> 01:56.867
HOW THE STORY ENDS.

01:56.992 --> 01:58.786
>> APPEARING OFF THE COAST OF

01:58.911 --> 02:00.746
GRIFFIN ROCK, THE PIRATE SHIP

02:00.871 --> 02:02.623
KNOWN AS  THE OAKEN CROW  FIRED

02:02.748 --> 02:04.666
ITS CANNONS.

02:04.792 --> 02:06.085
[ PEOPLE SCREAMING ]

02:06.209 --> 02:08.128
ITS BAND OF BUCCANEERS THEN CAME

02:08.253 --> 02:10.255
ASHORE TO PILLAGE THE TOWN,

02:10.380 --> 02:12.299
SETTING EVERYTHING ABLAZE.

02:15.761 --> 02:17.387
THE MOST IRREPLACEABLE OF THE

02:17.512 --> 02:19.139
BOOTY STOLEN THAT DAY WAS THE

02:19.264 --> 02:20.975
SETTLERS' BELL, WHICH HAD HUNG

02:21.100 --> 02:22.684
IN THE LIGHTHOUSE TOWER EVER

02:22.810 --> 02:24.394
SINCE THE TOWN'S FOUNDING IN

02:24.519 --> 02:26.647
1649.

02:26.772 --> 02:28.857
THE LOSS CONTINUES TO BE FELT TO

02:28.983 --> 02:29.691
THIS DAY.

02:29.817 --> 02:30.734
AS FOR THE PIRATES...

02:30.859 --> 02:32.027
>> PLEASE TELL ME THEY WERE

02:32.152 --> 02:33.528
PURSUED ACROSS THE HIGH SEAS AND

02:33.654 --> 02:34.488
BROUGHT TO JUSTICE.

02:34.613 --> 02:35.781
>> UH, I'LL HAVE TO FINISH

02:35.906 --> 02:36.448
LATER, GUYS.

02:36.573 --> 02:37.157
>> [ GROANS ]

02:37.282 --> 02:38.158
>> [ GROANS ]

02:38.283 --> 02:39.367
>> WELL, THAT IS DISAPPOINTING.

02:39.493 --> 02:42.663
>> ONE MORE CHAPTER, PLEASE?

02:42.788 --> 02:43.538
>> CAN'T.

02:43.664 --> 02:44.665
MY LAD PIONEER TROOP HAS A

02:44.790 --> 02:46.207
REHEARSAL FOR THE FOUNDERS' DAY

02:46.333 --> 02:47.250
CEREMONY TOMORROW.

02:47.375 --> 02:48.167
WE'RE HONORING THE

02:48.293 --> 02:49.252
ACCOMPLISHMENTS OF THE EARLY

02:49.377 --> 02:50.587
SETTLERS.

02:50.712 --> 02:51.880
>> ACCOMPLISHMENTS?

02:52.006 --> 02:53.548
>> WORKING TOGETHER TO BUILD

02:53.674 --> 02:54.549
SOMETHING NEW.

02:54.675 --> 02:56.468
"WE ARRIVED, WE SURVIVED, AND WE

02:56.593 --> 02:57.136
THRIVED."

02:57.260 --> 02:59.638
COOL MOTTO, HUH?

02:59.763 --> 03:01.098
>> SETTING UP CAMP ON A PRETTY

03:01.222 --> 03:02.349
ISLAND HARDLY SEEMS WORTH

03:02.474 --> 03:03.934
REMEMBERING.

03:04.059 --> 03:05.310
HUMANS SPEND TOO MUCH TIME

03:05.435 --> 03:06.645
THINKING ABOUT THE PAST.

03:06.770 --> 03:07.479
>> [ SIGHS ]

03:07.604 --> 03:08.981
YOU'RE MISSING THE POINT.

03:09.106 --> 03:09.564
SEE --

03:09.690 --> 03:10.273
>>  CODY.

03:10.398 --> 03:12.026
>> COMING!

03:21.493 --> 03:22.577
UH, I WAS JUST EXPLAINING

03:22.703 --> 03:23.829
FOUNDERS' DAY TO THE BOTS,

03:23.954 --> 03:24.830
AND --

03:24.955 --> 03:25.747
>> ABOUT THAT -- I'M AFRAID THE

03:25.873 --> 03:26.915
CEREMONY'S ON HOLD.

03:27.041 --> 03:28.750
STORM'S ABOUT TO MAKE LANDFALL.

03:28.876 --> 03:30.418
>> AWW.

03:30.544 --> 03:31.586
>> ALL RIGHT, TEAM.

03:31.712 --> 03:33.296
WE NEED TO BUTTON DOWN THE TOWN.

03:33.421 --> 03:35.423
[ ALARM BLARING ]

03:46.309 --> 03:47.728
>> RESCUE BOTS, ROLL TO THE

03:47.853 --> 03:49.771
RESCUE!

03:54.568 --> 03:56.195
[ WIND HOWLING ]

04:25.182 --> 04:27.684
>> [ SIGHS ]

04:27.809 --> 04:30.353
>> OW.

04:30.478 --> 04:32.773
[ DOORS CREAKING ]

04:53.334 --> 04:54.502
>> ABOUT TIME, BLADES.

04:54.628 --> 04:56.046
WHAT DID YOU DO -- WALK THE

04:56.171 --> 04:56.797
WHOLE WAY?

04:56.922 --> 04:59.258
>> HAD TO. SEE?

04:59.382 --> 05:01.135
>> BLADES, WERE YOU DAMAGED IN

05:01.260 --> 05:02.302
THE LINE OF DUTY?

05:02.427 --> 05:03.303
>> YES, I WAS.

05:03.428 --> 05:05.013
THREW MYSELF IN THE PATH OF AN

05:05.139 --> 05:05.680
AIRPLANE.

05:05.806 --> 05:06.765
SAVED A YOUNG MAN.

05:06.890 --> 05:08.391
>> A YOUNG MAN WHO GOT ALL

05:08.516 --> 05:09.851
GOOSHY EYES WITH DANI.

05:09.977 --> 05:13.063
>> HE DID NOT!

05:13.188 --> 05:14.689
>> GOOSHY EYES?

05:14.815 --> 05:15.816
SOUNDS PAINFUL.

05:15.941 --> 05:17.734
>> WE'LL HAVE GRAHAM STRAIGHTEN

05:17.859 --> 05:19.820
THAT ROTOR OUT WHEN WE GET HOME.

05:23.323 --> 05:24.866
>> NOW THAT I KNOW A BELL IS

05:24.992 --> 05:26.701
SUPPOSED TO BE IN THAT TOWER, IT

05:26.827 --> 05:28.495
LOOKS KIND OF EMPTY.

05:28.620 --> 05:29.913
>> THE TOWN JUST NEVER FELT

05:30.038 --> 05:31.165
RIGHT ABOUT INSTALLING A

05:31.290 --> 05:31.915
REPLACEMENT.

05:32.040 --> 05:32.916
>> WHY NOT?

05:33.041 --> 05:34.209
THEN EVERYONE COULD QUIT MOPING

05:34.334 --> 05:35.669
AND GET ON WITH THEIR LIVES.

05:35.794 --> 05:37.004
>> THE ORIGINAL BELL WAS

05:37.129 --> 05:38.046
SPECIAL, HEATWAVE.

05:38.172 --> 05:39.714
IT NEEDS TO BE REMEMBERED, NOT

05:39.840 --> 05:40.590
REPLACED.

05:40.715 --> 05:42.134
>> I UNDERSTAND PERFECTLY.

05:42.259 --> 05:43.677
PEOPLE GATHER ON FOUNDERS' DAY

05:43.802 --> 05:45.137
TO SHARE THEIR ANGER OVER THE

05:45.262 --> 05:46.554
THEFT OF PERSONAL PROPERTY.

05:46.680 --> 05:48.890
>> WELL, NOT EXACTLY.

05:49.016 --> 05:50.475
>> SO, WHAT  DID  HAPPEN TO THE

05:50.600 --> 05:52.311
PIRATES AFTER THEY TOOK OFF WITH

05:52.435 --> 05:53.270
THE BELL?

05:53.394 --> 05:54.271
>> THEY SAILED INTO A STORM THAT

05:54.395 --> 05:55.438
WAS PROBABLY A LOT LIKE THIS

05:55.563 --> 05:56.315
ONE.

05:56.439 --> 05:56.815
NOBODY EVER HEARD FROM THEM

05:56.940 --> 05:58.900
AGAIN.

06:02.279 --> 06:03.905
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

06:04.031 --> 06:05.824
>> ALL RIGHT, EVERYONE.

06:05.949 --> 06:07.659
AFTER WE SECURE THE MARINA, WE

06:07.784 --> 06:09.577
SHOULD BE DONE.

06:13.623 --> 06:15.458
[ GRUNTING ]

06:19.462 --> 06:20.922
[ GASPS ]

06:21.048 --> 06:22.841
[ CRATES CREAKING ]

06:23.884 --> 06:25.468
WHOSE BRIGHT IDEA WAS IT TO

06:25.593 --> 06:27.386
STACK CONTAINERS FOUR HIGH?

06:27.512 --> 06:28.847
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

06:28.972 --> 06:30.640
DOUBLE-TIME IT, TEAM!

06:32.142 --> 06:33.768
>> [ GRUNTS ]

06:37.564 --> 06:37.981
>> OHH!

06:38.106 --> 06:38.732
>> INCOMING!

06:38.857 --> 06:39.566
>> LOOK OUT!

06:39.691 --> 06:41.026
>> AAH!

06:48.075 --> 06:49.576
AAH! AAH!

06:49.701 --> 06:50.493
>> CODY, NO!

06:50.618 --> 06:51.370
>> HANG ON!

06:51.494 --> 06:53.372
LET'S GET TO OUR BOAT!

07:08.345 --> 07:10.013
>> CODY! CODY, DO YOU READ?!

07:10.138 --> 07:10.805
[ Static ]

07:10.931 --> 07:12.599
[ WIND HOWLING ]

07:14.976 --> 07:16.228
>> Dad?

07:16.353 --> 07:18.355
>> ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

07:18.521 --> 07:20.565
>> I THINK SO.

07:20.690 --> 07:21.942
BUT WE'RE DRIFTING AWAY FROM THE

07:22.067 --> 07:22.901
ISLAND.

07:23.026 --> 07:23.777
>> We'll find you. I promise!

07:23.902 --> 07:24.736
[ Static ]

07:24.861 --> 07:26.071
>> DAD, YOU'RE BREAKING UP!

07:26.196 --> 07:27.530
>> WE'RE APPROACHING THE LIMIT

07:27.655 --> 07:28.698
OF COMMUNICATION RANGE.

07:28.823 --> 07:30.325
>> CHIEF, DON'T WORRY.

07:30.450 --> 07:31.910
WE'LL KEEP CODY SAFE.

07:32.035 --> 07:34.454
>> Stay [Static] strong!

07:40.377 --> 07:41.711
>> WE CAN'T DO ANYTHING?

07:41.836 --> 07:43.504
>> IT'S TOO UNSAFE FOR ANY BOAT

07:43.630 --> 07:44.798
OUT THERE, OR PLANE.

07:44.923 --> 07:46.216
>> WE CAN TRUST THE BOTS.

07:46.341 --> 07:47.384
CODY WILL BE FINE.

07:47.508 --> 07:49.094
>> AS SOON AS THE STORM BREAKS,

07:49.219 --> 07:50.929
WE'LL GRAB HIM.

08:00.688 --> 08:02.732
>> THE STORM IS FINALLY PASSING.

08:04.025 --> 08:05.402
>> MORE LIKE  WE'RE  PASSING OUT

08:05.526 --> 08:07.321
OF THE STORM.

08:07.446 --> 08:08.488
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

08:08.613 --> 08:10.240
GRIFFIN ROCK IS STILL GETTING

08:10.365 --> 08:11.199
HAMMERED.

08:11.325 --> 08:12.742
>> THAT MEANS NO SEARCH PARTY.

08:12.867 --> 08:14.661
>> WE COULD BE OUT HERE DRIFTING

08:14.786 --> 08:16.121
FOR DAYS OR WEEKS OR --

08:16.246 --> 08:17.705
>> 12 MINUTES, 17 SECONDS,

08:17.831 --> 08:19.624
ASSUMING WE MAINTAIN OUR CURRENT

08:19.749 --> 08:21.542
RATE OF SPEED, OF COURSE.

08:28.091 --> 08:29.550
>> LOOKS UNINHABITED.

08:29.676 --> 08:31.761
>> YOU KNOW WHAT THIS MAKES US?

08:31.886 --> 08:33.347
>> INHABITANTS?

08:33.472 --> 08:35.015
>> CASTAWAYS!

08:35.140 --> 08:36.183
ISN'T THAT COOL?!

08:36.308 --> 08:38.143
>> YOU KNOW WHAT WOULD BE EVEN

08:38.268 --> 08:38.977
COOLER?

08:39.102 --> 08:40.561
IF MY ROTOR WEREN'T BENT.

08:40.687 --> 08:42.356
THEN I COULD FLY FOR HELP.

08:42.481 --> 08:43.940
>> SO, WHAT'S OUR NEXT MOVE?

08:44.065 --> 08:45.566
>> WELL, WE PROMISED THE CHIEF

08:45.692 --> 08:47.652
WE'D KEEP CODY SAFE.

08:50.030 --> 08:51.698
[ BIRDS CAWING ]

08:51.823 --> 08:53.992
>> BUT WHO'S GONNA KEEP  US  SAFE?

08:58.205 --> 08:59.956
[ CAWING CONTINUES ]

09:02.876 --> 09:05.670
[ WATER RUNNING ]

09:05.795 --> 09:07.381
>> HUH. THIS SHOULD WORK.

09:07.506 --> 09:08.631
>> WORK FOR WHAT?

09:08.756 --> 09:09.674
>> A SHELTER.

09:09.799 --> 09:11.551
FRESH WATER, DRY GROUND, AND

09:11.676 --> 09:13.387
CLOSE ENOUGH TO THE BEACH TO

09:13.512 --> 09:15.055
WATCH FOR PASSING SHIPS.

09:15.180 --> 09:16.639
>> UH, SHELTER -- RIGHT.

09:16.764 --> 09:18.350
ONE SHELTER COMING UP!

09:18.475 --> 09:20.894
RESCUE BOTS, ROLL TO THE RESCUE!

09:23.146 --> 09:24.105
>> I CAN HELP!

09:24.231 --> 09:26.274
>> I'M AFRAID THIS IS A JOB FOR

09:26.400 --> 09:27.484
HEAVY MACHINERY.

09:27.608 --> 09:29.652
>> WHY DON'T YOU REST UP, CODY?

09:29.777 --> 09:31.446
>> OVER NEAR THE STREAM,

09:31.571 --> 09:32.364
PERHAPS.

09:32.489 --> 09:34.199
>> SAFELY OUT OF HARM'S WAY.

09:34.324 --> 09:35.158
>> HMM...

09:35.283 --> 09:38.495
WE'LL NEED ROCKS, MUD, LOGS --

09:38.619 --> 09:40.121
MORE PRIMITIVE MATERIALS THAN

09:40.247 --> 09:40.955
I'M USED TO.

09:41.081 --> 09:42.874
SHOULD BE INTERESTING.

09:58.432 --> 10:00.100
>> HIP, HIP.

10:03.103 --> 10:05.230
>> [ SQUAWKING ]

10:05.355 --> 10:07.023
>> [ GASPS ]

10:09.984 --> 10:11.361
AAH!

10:11.486 --> 10:12.446
CHASE!

10:12.571 --> 10:14.155
I THOUGHT YOU WERE A PREDATOR

10:14.281 --> 10:15.865
WITH A TASTE FOR HELICOPTERS.

10:15.990 --> 10:17.117
>> NO DOUBT OUR PRESENCE HERE

10:17.242 --> 10:18.326
HAS UNSETTLED THE INDIGENOUS

10:18.452 --> 10:18.952
WILDLIFE.

10:19.077 --> 10:21.788
>> [ SQUAWKING ]

10:21.913 --> 10:23.582
>> IT'S COMING FOR US!

10:23.706 --> 10:26.585
>> [ SQUAWKS ]

10:26.709 --> 10:30.046
[ SQUAWKING ]

10:30.171 --> 10:32.382
>> WE TELL NO ONE OF THIS.

10:32.507 --> 10:34.301
>> AGREED.

10:42.058 --> 10:43.768
>> [ GASPS ]

10:44.436 --> 10:45.770
>> SPRUNG FROM NATURE'S

10:45.895 --> 10:47.397
RESOURCES, YET WITH ALL THE

10:47.522 --> 10:48.982
SOOTHING COMFORTS OF HOME.

10:49.107 --> 10:53.653
WE CALL IT "ISLAND FORTRESS."

10:53.778 --> 10:54.737
[ CREAKING ]

10:54.862 --> 10:58.325
[ CRASH! CRASH! CRASH! ]

10:58.450 --> 10:59.784
[ THUD! ]

10:59.909 --> 11:00.452
[ GROANS ]

11:00.577 --> 11:01.453
>> ISLAND FLAWED.

11:01.578 --> 11:03.163
>> I KNEW IT WOULDN'T WORK.

11:03.288 --> 11:04.414
>> IT'S OKAY, GUYS.

11:04.539 --> 11:06.249
I BUILT MY OWN.

11:09.794 --> 11:11.254
>> SIMPLE YET FUNCTIONAL.

11:11.379 --> 11:13.131
>> HOW'D YOU LEARN HOW TO BUILD

11:13.256 --> 11:13.756
THAT?

11:13.881 --> 11:14.882
>> LAD PIONEERS.

11:15.008 --> 11:16.843
SEE? IT  DOES  PAY TO LEARN HOW

11:16.968 --> 11:18.803
THINGS WERE DONE IN THE PAST.

11:18.928 --> 11:21.139
>> AND THAT QUAINT CAMPFIRE.

11:21.264 --> 11:22.890
>> HEAT CAUSED BY A LITTLE

11:23.016 --> 11:24.976
FRICTION AND A LOT OF PATIENCE.

11:27.145 --> 11:29.022
>> I WANT TO BE A LAD PIONEER!

11:29.147 --> 11:30.982
>> YOU CAN BE A  BOT  PIONEER...

11:31.107 --> 11:32.233
WHEN WE GET HOME.

11:32.359 --> 11:34.110
BUT RIGHT NOW, IT'S ABOUT

11:34.235 --> 11:35.487
DINNERTIME, SO...

11:35.612 --> 11:37.405
>> FOOD -- YOU NEED FOOD.

11:37.531 --> 11:39.740
RESCUE BOTS, ROLL TO THE RESCUE.

11:41.576 --> 11:42.452
>> WAIT!

11:42.577 --> 11:44.120
GUYS!

11:44.245 --> 11:45.913
[ SIGHS ]

11:53.754 --> 11:55.756
>> WHERE ARE ALL THE -- WHAT ARE

11:55.882 --> 11:57.342
THE CREATURES CALLED?

11:57.467 --> 11:58.301
>> CLAMS.

11:58.426 --> 11:59.760
THE BOOK I READ SAID THEY LIVE

11:59.886 --> 12:00.679
IN THE SAND.

12:00.803 --> 12:02.597
MAYBE WE HAVE TO DIG DEEPER.

12:10.938 --> 12:11.231
>> GOTCHA!

12:11.356 --> 12:11.981
[ SNAP! ]

12:12.106 --> 12:13.274
AAH!

12:19.155 --> 12:21.366
>> HEY, I SCORED AN EGG!

12:21.491 --> 12:22.367
>> HUH?!

12:22.492 --> 12:23.702
[ WHISTLE! ]

12:23.826 --> 12:24.285
[ CLANK! ]

12:24.411 --> 12:24.911
>> AAH!

12:25.036 --> 12:26.580
WA-A-A-A-A-H!

12:29.207 --> 12:30.958
>> SORRY!

12:31.710 --> 12:34.003
>> I UNDERSTAND THESE ARE QUITE

12:34.128 --> 12:35.754
A DELICACY IN FRANCE.

12:35.880 --> 12:37.465
>> GUYS, YOU WOULDN'T BELIEVE

12:37.591 --> 12:39.008
THE NUMBER OF FISH IN THAT

12:39.133 --> 12:39.758
STREAM!

12:39.884 --> 12:40.885
>> UM, I'M CONFUSED.

12:41.010 --> 12:42.637
DID  WE  ROLL TO THE RESCUE, OR

12:42.761 --> 12:44.472
DID CODY?

12:44.598 --> 12:45.682
>> DON'T FEEL BAD.

12:45.806 --> 12:46.600
YOU TRIED.

12:46.725 --> 12:48.059
HEY, YOU KNOW WHAT I REALLY

12:48.184 --> 12:48.602
NEED?

12:48.727 --> 12:50.645
FIREWOOD!

12:58.653 --> 12:59.778
>> AH, TOASTY.

12:59.904 --> 13:01.322
NEED ANYTHING ELSE?

13:01.448 --> 13:03.658
>> NOPE. I'M GOOD.

13:03.782 --> 13:06.119
>> SO, UH...

13:06.244 --> 13:07.786
WHAT WOULD A BOT PIONEER DO

13:07.912 --> 13:09.414
NEXT?

13:09.539 --> 13:11.291
>> UH, WE COULD TELL SPOOKY

13:11.416 --> 13:11.999
STORIES!

13:12.125 --> 13:13.334
I KNOW A GOOD ONE.

13:13.460 --> 13:15.503
FIVE FRIENDS WENT INTO A DARK

13:15.629 --> 13:16.963
AND CREEPY FOREST.

13:17.088 --> 13:18.089
[ OWL HOOTS ]

13:18.214 --> 13:19.882
>> FIRE NEEDS MORE WOOD!

13:20.007 --> 13:20.717
>> WAIT!

13:20.841 --> 13:23.094
DO YOU SEE WHAT THAT IS?

13:23.219 --> 13:24.387
>> UM...OAK?

13:24.512 --> 13:26.765
>> IT'S A CROW -- LIKE THE

13:26.889 --> 13:28.600
FIGUREHEAD ON THE PIRATE SHIP!

13:28.725 --> 13:30.602
>> THE ONE THAT TOOK YOUR BELL?

13:30.727 --> 13:32.520
>> COULD THOSE PIRATES HAVE BEEN

13:32.646 --> 13:34.272
SHIPWRECKED ON  THIS  ISLAND?!

13:34.397 --> 13:36.149
>> IF THEIR STORM WAS OF EQUAL

13:36.274 --> 13:37.984
MAGNITUDE TO OURS, IT IS QUITE

13:38.109 --> 13:38.901
FEASIBLE.

13:39.026 --> 13:40.487
>> YOU KNOW WHAT THIS MEANS?

13:40.612 --> 13:42.656
>> THE PIRATES ARE STILL HERE!

13:42.781 --> 13:44.365
>> NOT AFTER 200 YEARS.

13:44.491 --> 13:46.701
BUT IF THEIR SHIP IS STILL HERE,

13:46.825 --> 13:48.411
THE BELL COULD BE, TOO.

13:48.536 --> 13:50.037
WHERE'D YOU FIND THAT WOOD?

13:50.163 --> 13:51.706
>> UP A RIDGE 100 METERS THAT

13:51.830 --> 13:52.749
WAY.

13:52.873 --> 13:54.250
>> LET'S CHECK IT OUT.

13:54.375 --> 13:56.169
>> WHOA. HOLD ON, MR. PIONEER.

13:56.294 --> 13:58.087
IT'S TOO TREACHEROUS UP THERE,

13:58.212 --> 13:59.547
EVEN WITH OUR LIGHTS.

13:59.673 --> 14:00.923
>> HEATWAVE'S RIGHT.

14:01.048 --> 14:02.925
WE'LL LOOK IN THE MORNING.

14:03.050 --> 14:04.803
>> BESIDES, FIVE FRIENDS GOING

14:04.927 --> 14:06.763
INTO A DARK AND CREEPY FOREST --

14:06.887 --> 14:08.431
I DON'T WANT TO BE SOMEONE

14:08.556 --> 14:11.017
ELSE'S CAMPFIRE STORY.

14:11.142 --> 14:12.686
>> OKAY.

14:24.698 --> 14:25.948
>> CODY, DO YOU READ?

14:26.073 --> 14:28.075
CODY BURNS, CAN YOU HEAR ME?

14:28.201 --> 14:30.286
[ ELECTRONIC BEEP ]

14:30.411 --> 14:31.621
>> DAD, DON'T WORRY.

14:31.746 --> 14:33.122
WITH THIS MANY VOLUNTEERS

14:33.247 --> 14:35.166
SEARCHING, WE'LL FIND THEM.

14:44.091 --> 14:44.925
>> ALL RIGHT.

14:45.051 --> 14:46.427
THIS IS WHERE WE FOUND MOST OF

14:46.553 --> 14:47.303
THE FIREWOOD.

14:47.428 --> 14:48.179
>> SPREAD OUT.

14:48.304 --> 14:49.723
LOOK FOR ANYTHING THAT COULD

14:49.848 --> 14:51.599
HAVE COME FROM THE SHIP.

14:58.606 --> 14:59.399
[ WHOOSH! ]

14:59.524 --> 14:59.940
AAH!

15:00.066 --> 15:01.234
>> CODY!

15:01.359 --> 15:03.737
>> CODY, WHERE ARE YOU?!

15:09.826 --> 15:10.117
>> CODY!

15:10.243 --> 15:10.827
>> CODY!

15:10.951 --> 15:11.369
>> PLEASE RESPOND!

15:11.494 --> 15:11.828
>> CODY!

15:11.952 --> 15:12.495
>> CODY!

15:12.620 --> 15:13.538
>> LAD PIONEER!

15:13.663 --> 15:14.581
[ WHOOSH! ]

15:14.706 --> 15:17.375
>> Both: AAH!

15:17.500 --> 15:19.293
>> HEATWAVE?

15:19.419 --> 15:21.003
>> BOULDER?

15:22.004 --> 15:24.215
>> Both: AAH!

15:24.340 --> 15:26.342
>> WHOA!

15:26.467 --> 15:28.094
AAH!

15:28.219 --> 15:29.470
AAH!

15:29.596 --> 15:30.054
>> UGH!

15:30.179 --> 15:32.807
>> UGH!

15:32.932 --> 15:34.893
>> EVERYONE ALL RIGHT?

15:35.017 --> 15:36.561
>> I'LL LET YOU KNOW ONCE MY

15:36.686 --> 15:37.687
ALTIMETER SETTLES.

15:37.812 --> 15:39.146
>> WHAT DID WE JUST FALL

15:39.272 --> 15:40.147
THROUGH?

15:40.273 --> 15:41.858
>> A SECRET HATCHWAY BUILT BY

15:41.982 --> 15:42.901
THE PIRATES!

15:43.025 --> 15:43.693
>> CODY!

15:43.818 --> 15:44.985
>> YOU HAD US WORRIED.

15:45.111 --> 15:45.862
ARE YOU HURT?

15:45.986 --> 15:46.863
>> I'M FINE.

15:46.987 --> 15:48.615
BUT YOU'LL NEVER BELIEVE WHAT I

15:48.740 --> 15:49.908
FOUND.

15:50.950 --> 15:52.326
TAKE A LOOK!

15:52.452 --> 15:54.120
>> UNBELIEVABLE.

15:54.245 --> 15:56.790
>>  THE OAKEN CROW.

15:56.915 --> 15:58.416
ASTONISHING.

15:58.541 --> 16:00.209
>> LOOKS LIKE IT CAME IN THROUGH

16:00.334 --> 16:02.002
THERE BUT THEN WAS BLOCKED IN,

16:02.128 --> 16:03.838
PROBABLY FROM A ROCKSLIDE.

16:03.963 --> 16:04.756
>> COME ON!

16:04.881 --> 16:05.715
LET'S SEE IF THE BELL'S ON

16:05.840 --> 16:07.634
BOARD.

16:07.759 --> 16:09.427
>> YOU'RE THINKING WHAT I'M

16:09.552 --> 16:10.177
THINKING?

16:10.303 --> 16:11.304
>> YES.

16:11.429 --> 16:12.096
NO.

16:12.221 --> 16:14.140
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

16:14.265 --> 16:15.475
>> THIS IS THE REASON THE

16:15.600 --> 16:16.976
PIRATES WERE NEVER HEARD FROM

16:17.101 --> 16:17.811
AGAIN.

16:17.936 --> 16:19.103
>> THEY NEVER GOT OFF THE

16:19.228 --> 16:19.729
ISLAND.

16:19.854 --> 16:20.855
>> SO?

16:20.980 --> 16:22.273
>> THERE'S A HIGH PROBABILITY

16:22.398 --> 16:23.691
WE'LL  NEVER GET OFF THE ISLAN,

16:23.817 --> 16:24.484
EITHER.

16:24.609 --> 16:25.359
>> THAT'S NOT WHAT I WAS

16:25.485 --> 16:28.070
THINKING -- UNTIL NOW.

16:28.195 --> 16:30.448
>> [ GRUNTS ]

16:30.573 --> 16:32.408
[ GASPS ]

16:38.915 --> 16:40.500
THERE YOU ARE!

16:42.502 --> 16:43.670
AWESOME, ISN'T IT?!

16:43.795 --> 16:45.129
>> A TRUE WORK OF ART.

16:45.254 --> 16:46.965
>> SITTING HERE ALL THIS TIME,

16:47.089 --> 16:48.549
JUST WAITING TO BE FOUND.

16:48.675 --> 16:50.468
>> A SPLENDID DISCOVERY, CODY.

16:50.593 --> 16:51.886
>> I CAN'T BELIEVE THE

16:52.011 --> 16:53.554
SETTLERS' BELL CAN FINALLY

16:53.680 --> 16:55.556
RETURN HOME.

16:55.682 --> 16:56.808
WHAT'S WRONG?

16:56.933 --> 16:59.101
>> IT'S JUST THAT [SIGHS] NO

16:59.226 --> 17:00.728
TELLING HOW LONG WE'LL BE

17:00.854 --> 17:01.771
MAROONED HERE.

17:01.896 --> 17:03.230
>> IT'S A BIG OCEAN...

17:03.356 --> 17:04.774
AND A RATHER SMALL ISLAND.

17:04.899 --> 17:05.900
>> COME ON, GUYS!

17:06.025 --> 17:07.735
BOT PIONEERS ARE NOT ALLOWED TO

17:07.861 --> 17:08.736
LOSE HOPE!

17:08.862 --> 17:10.321
WE HAVE TO BE RESOURCEFUL, JUST

17:10.446 --> 17:11.823
LIKE THE EARLY SETTLERS.

17:11.948 --> 17:13.491
>> WHAT ARE WE DOING?!

17:13.616 --> 17:14.575
CODY'S RIGHT!

17:14.701 --> 17:16.076
WE SHOULDN'T BE GIVING UP SO

17:16.202 --> 17:16.911
EASILY!

17:17.036 --> 17:18.037
>> WE CAN BE RESOURCEFUL.

17:18.162 --> 17:19.497
>> PERHAPS WE COULD BUILD A

17:19.622 --> 17:20.832
SEAWORTHY CRAFT AND SAIL

17:20.957 --> 17:21.708
OURSELVES HOME.

17:21.833 --> 17:22.542
>>  BUILD  ONE?

17:22.667 --> 17:24.293
WE'RE  STANDING  ON ONE!

17:24.418 --> 17:25.795
>>  THE OAKEN CROW?

17:25.920 --> 17:27.046
BUT SHE'S LANDLOCKED.

17:27.171 --> 17:28.756
>> I'M GUESSING THAT GETTING HER

17:28.882 --> 17:30.550
OUT WAS TOO BIG OF A JOB FOR THE

17:30.675 --> 17:32.301
PIRATES, BUT...

17:32.426 --> 17:33.219
>> NOT FOR US!

17:33.344 --> 17:34.178
>> AGREED!

17:34.303 --> 17:35.555
WHILE KNOWING HOW THINGS WERE

17:35.680 --> 17:37.139
DONE IN THE PAST IS HELPFUL,

17:37.264 --> 17:38.850
NOTHING BEATS A STATE-OF-THE-ART

17:38.975 --> 17:39.809
RESCUE BOT.

17:39.934 --> 17:41.978
>> WHAT DO YOU SAY, HEATWAVE?

17:42.102 --> 17:43.730
>> I SAY IT'S HIGH TIME  WE  DO

17:43.855 --> 17:45.648
SOMETHING FOR  YOU,  LIKE GET YOU

17:45.773 --> 17:47.859
HOME.

17:47.984 --> 17:50.570
>> CODY! CODY, COME IN, PLEASE!

17:50.695 --> 17:51.738
[ Static ]

17:51.863 --> 17:53.447
CODY BURNS, PLEASE COME IN!

17:53.573 --> 17:54.741
[ Static ]

17:54.866 --> 17:56.116
>> THEY MUST STILL BE OUT OF

17:56.242 --> 17:56.993
RANGE.

17:57.117 --> 17:58.452
>> THEY COULD BE ANYWHERE.

17:58.578 --> 17:59.662
>> I'LL TRY FOR A WHILE.

17:59.787 --> 18:00.538
[ RADIO BEEPS ]

18:00.663 --> 18:02.456
CODY, ARE YOU THERE?

18:02.582 --> 18:04.375
PLEASE, COME IN.

18:07.378 --> 18:09.088
[ BOTS GRUNTING ]

18:15.261 --> 18:17.096
[ GRUNTING CONTINUES ]

18:24.562 --> 18:26.397
[ BOTS GRUNTING ]

18:31.360 --> 18:33.362
[ ADVENTUROUS MUSIC PLAYING ]

18:57.887 --> 18:58.930
[ ALL CHEER ]

18:59.055 --> 18:59.931
>> YES!

19:00.056 --> 19:02.100
>> WE ARRIVED, WE SURVIVED, AND

19:02.224 --> 19:03.476
WE THRIVED.

19:03.601 --> 19:05.436
>> AVAST, ME HEARTIES!

19:05.561 --> 19:07.814
HOIST THE JIB AND RAISE THE

19:07.939 --> 19:08.773
YARDARM!

19:08.898 --> 19:10.524
OR THE OTHER WAY AROUND!

19:10.650 --> 19:11.692
>> AYE, MATEY!

19:11.818 --> 19:14.070
SET SAIL FOR GRIFFIN ROCK...

19:14.194 --> 19:16.280
WHICHEVER WAY THAT IS.

19:20.576 --> 19:22.703
>> UNDERSTOOD.

19:22.829 --> 19:23.788
THANK YOU FOR YOUR EFFORTS.

19:23.913 --> 19:24.538
[ Static ]

19:24.664 --> 19:26.124
PLANE'S HEADING BACK.

19:26.248 --> 19:27.541
IT'S GETTING TOO DARK.

19:27.667 --> 19:29.418
WE'LL BE LOSING THE OTHER BOATS

19:29.543 --> 19:30.210
SOON, TOO.

19:30.336 --> 19:31.004
>> [ SIGHS ]

19:31.129 --> 19:31.879
COME ON, BUDDY.

19:32.005 --> 19:34.256
WHERE ARE YOU?

19:34.381 --> 19:35.257
[ BELL TOLLING IN DISTANCE ]

19:35.382 --> 19:37.844
[ BOTH GASP ]

19:37.969 --> 19:39.219
>> DO YOU HEAR THAT?

19:39.345 --> 19:40.847
>> IT SOUNDS LIKE A BELL.

19:40.972 --> 19:42.807
>> IT'S COMING FROM OVER THERE.

19:42.932 --> 19:44.851
[ TOLLING CONTINUES ]

19:49.522 --> 19:51.315
>> Cody, can you hear me?

19:51.440 --> 19:52.066
>> DAD?!

19:52.191 --> 19:52.775
>> Cody!

19:52.900 --> 19:54.152
Are you all right?!

19:54.276 --> 19:55.028
>> WE ARE!

19:55.153 --> 19:56.904
>> I-If you're in range, you

19:57.030 --> 19:57.989
must be close.

19:58.114 --> 19:59.281
>> DAD, WE FOUND THE

19:59.406 --> 20:00.324
SETTLERS' BELL!

20:00.449 --> 20:01.450
CAN YOU HEAR IT?!

20:01.575 --> 20:03.536
>> SETTLERS' BELL?

20:03.661 --> 20:04.871
[ TOLLING CONTINUES ]

20:04.996 --> 20:06.539
>> THAT'S NOT ALL THEY FOUND.

20:06.664 --> 20:08.166
LOOK!

20:15.506 --> 20:17.466
>> OH, I WAS SO WORRIED ABOUT

20:17.591 --> 20:18.384
YOU.

20:18.509 --> 20:19.844
THANK YOU FOR TAKING CARE OF

20:19.969 --> 20:20.761
CODY.

20:20.887 --> 20:22.138
>> WE ALL TOOK CARE OF EACH

20:22.262 --> 20:23.514
OTHER.

20:24.932 --> 20:26.893
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

20:41.365 --> 20:43.492
[ BELL TOLLING ]

20:46.079 --> 20:48.081
[ LAUGHTER ]

20:56.714 --> 20:59.759
>> [ LAUGHS ]

20:59.884 --> 21:01.677
>> WHAT? HE'S A...GOOD PILOT.

21:01.802 --> 21:02.720
>> [ SCOFFS ]

21:02.845 --> 21:03.846
LET'S HOPE SO.

21:03.971 --> 21:06.224
>> DOES HE HAVE A SISTER?

21:06.348 --> 21:07.433
>> THIS WILL REQUIRE A NEW

21:07.558 --> 21:08.726
CHAPTER TO BE WRITTEN IN THE

21:08.851 --> 21:09.936
GRIFFIN ROCK HISTORY BOOK.

21:10.061 --> 21:11.645
>> MAYBE THEY'LL MENTION US.

21:11.771 --> 21:13.480
>> THEY'D BETTER.

21:13.606 --> 21:15.441
>> SO, WHEN ARE WE HOLDING OUR

21:15.566 --> 21:17.193
FIRST BOT PIONEERS MEETING?

21:17.317 --> 21:18.945
I NOMINATE MYSELF AS TROOP

21:19.070 --> 21:19.612
LEADER.

21:19.737 --> 21:22.364
ALL IN FAVOR?

21:22.489 --> 21:23.449
GUYS?

21:23.574 --> 21:25.701
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO SAY, "AYE" OR

21:25.826 --> 21:27.912
JUST NOD.

21:28.037 --> 21:29.872
GUYS?

21:29.997 --> 21:32.750
[ TOLLING CONTINUES ]
